# Toggle preview

This scenario verifies that `C-p` toggles the preview pane.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init alpha (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R alpha -m "alpha commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh cli -r alpha" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 100 -y 8 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0

The preview should be visible initially.

    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session:                               ┃
  3/3 | [C-r] repo: none               ┃
▌⬤ runner                              ┃
 ⬤ ui                                  ┃
   alpha                               ┃
                                       ┃
                                       ┃
                                       ┃
```

Pressing `C-p` should hide the preview and allow the list to use the full width.

    :k C-p
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session:                                                                                           ┃
  3/3 | [C-r] repo: none                                                                           ┃
▌⬤ runner                                                                                          ┃
 ⬤ ui                                                                                              ┃
   alpha                                    alpha                                                  ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

Pressing `C-p` again should restore the preview.

    :k C-p
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session:                               ┃
  3/3 | [C-r] repo: none               ┃
▌⬤ runner                              ┃
 ⬤ ui                                  ┃
   alpha                               ┃
                                       ┃
                                       ┃
                                       ┃
```

